Job Description


Copywriting for NUU Mobile will lead the strategic storytelling responsibility in creating original, culturally vibrant, brand engagement: from top level campaign concepts, to arrange media advertising, and everything in between.
Play an instrumental role in shaping the expression of the NUU Mobile brand.
Bring ideas to life and convey our marketing messages to our target audiences.
Execute and shepherd concepts from conception and executive buy-in through all stages of creative development, production and post-production—ensuring faithful execution, quality, and brand consistency all the way.
Seek to push the brand and our marketing practice into new media, experimenting, testing and tracking.
Qualifications

Degree in Fine Arts, Communication Design, Advertising or equivalent practical experience.
5+ years of writing and creative direction experience at a creative agency;
Exceptional conceptual and written storytelling talent;
Proven experience developing strategically grounded, creative ideas across digital and traditional media, for major consumer brands;
A strong and diverse portfolio of original advertising and brand engagement work, including digital, video, and new media;
Expert understanding of creative considerations across print, website, mobile, online advertising, social media, video, and so on;
Ability to thoughtfully and persuasively articulate creative concepts to cross-functional teams;
Proficiency in creative and productivity applications: Photoshop, InDesign, Keynote/PowerPoint/Google Slides;
Experience in technology, consumer technology or consumer lifestyle categories;
Travelling is required and will stay in USA at least 6 months per year.

Job Responsibilities

Develop creative content strategy to meet client's marketing needs;
Create contents on digital platforms, including Facebook, Instagram, Weibo etc.;
To ensure all copy and information is accurate and meets commercial standard;
Research online behaviours and trends of the target audience
Monitor and report SEO performance and metrics, using web analytics tools and dashboards
Keeping updated with industry trends
Support the Business Manager on strategic projects as assigned

Job Requirements:

Minimum 1 years copywriting experience in writing;
Able to write excellent and stylish Cantonese;
Creative, willing to learn, self-initiative & motivated, responsible, supportive and able to work under pressure, independently and over time;
Good team player with excellent interpersonal and communication skills
Stay updated on creative trends *Immediate availability is preferred

Responsibilities:

 -Work as a part of our social media team to develop well social media practice;

- Create innovative & attention-grabbing copy for our clients’ pages e.g. Facebook, Instagram, Online Buzz; 

- Aspire to receive thousands of “Likes” and positive “Comments” by netizens on every one of your creative feeds in our social media websites;

- Support the team of the creative solutions, digital marketing strategy for client’s projects especially in online advertising and social media campaigns;

- Work together with creative team to develop the best digital solutions for clients, also closely work together with design and technical team for production;

- Prepare daily documents and presentation accordingly to client’s requirements and provide appropriate suggestions / solutions based on client’s enquiries.



Requirements:

